The adoption of multi-die designs is rapidly on the rise to push past reticle limits, increase performance, improve system power, and accelerate time-to-market. Having a solid multi-die architecture specification necessitates a data-driven design space exploration methodology and tooling for meeting power and performance goals and using models to simulate interconnects, workloads, and more. This paper describes how virtual prototyping and AI-driven design space exploration and analysis can accelerate design time.